{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013SrTmmZwhKmqDXu2yafmVu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→\"\"\"Grid hashing kernel for spatial partitioning of SPH particles.\n     2→\n     3→Compiles physics/kernels/hash_sort.cu via CuPy RawModule and provides\n     4→functions to upload GridParams to ``__constant__ GridParams c_grid`` and\n     5→launch the ``K_CalcHash`` kernel.\n     6→\n     7→Grid sizing (from acceptance criteria)\n     8→--------------------------------------\n     9→- grid_min = (-1, -1, -1), grid_max = (1, 1, 1)\n    10→- cell_size = h = 0.04\n    11→- grid_res  = 50 per axis\n    12→- grid_delta = (25, 25, 25)   (= grid_res / grid_size = 50/2)\n    13→- num_cells  = 125000          (= 50^3)\n    14→\"\"\"\n    15→\n    16→from __future__ import annotations\n    17→\n    18→import os\n    19→from typing import Optional, Tuple\n    20→\n    21→import cupy\n    22→import numpy as np\n    23→\n    24→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    25→# Grid constants\n    26→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    27→\n    28→GRID_MIN = np.array([-1.0, -1.0, -1.0], dtype=np.float32)\n    29→GRID_MAX = np.array([1.0, 1.0, 1.0], dtype=np.float32)\n    30→CELL_SIZE = np.float32(0.04)\n    31→GRID_RES = np.array([50, 50, 50], dtype=np.int32)\n    32→GRID_DELTA = np.array([25.0, 25.0, 25.0], dtype=np.float32)  # grid_res / grid_size\n    33→NUM_CELLS = 125_000  # 50 * 50 * 50\n    34→\n    35→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    36→# Numpy dtype matching ``struct GridParams`` in common.cuh\n    37→#\n    38→# struct GridParams {\n    39→#     float3 grid_min;    // 12 bytes\n    40→#     float3 grid_max;    // 12 bytes\n    41→#     int3   grid_res;    // 12 bytes\n    42→#     float3 grid_delta;  // 12 bytes\n    43→#     int    num_cells;   //  4 bytes\n    44→# };                      // Total: 52 bytes\n    45→#\n    46→# CUDA float3/int3 are 12 bytes with no trailing pad. align=False required.\n    47→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    48→\n    49→GRID_PARAMS_DTYPE = np.dtype(\n    50→    [\n    51→        (\"grid_min\", np.float32, (3,)),\n    52→        (\"grid_max\", np.float32, (3,)),\n    53→        (\"grid_res\", np.int32, (3,)),\n    54→        (\"grid_delta\", np.float32, (3,)),\n    55→        (\"num_cells\", np.int32),\n    56→    ],\n    57→    align=False,\n    58→)\n    59→\n    60→assert GRID_PARAMS_DTYPE.itemsize == 52, (\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e01bb850-3d98-461b-825e-005d7a10b01f","uuid":"081d0060-c84e-401e-acfb-b63446461d69","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/hash_sort.py","content":"\"\"\"Grid hashing kernel for spatial partitioning of SPH particles.\n\nCompiles physics/kernels/hash_sort.cu via CuPy RawModule and provides\nfunctions to upload GridParams to ``__constant__ GridParams c_grid`` and\nlaunch the ``K_CalcHash`` kernel.\n\nGrid sizing (from acceptance criteria)\n--------------------------------------\n- grid_min = (-1, -1, -1), grid_max = (1, 1, 1)\n- cell_size = h = 0.04\n- grid_res  = 50 per axis\n- grid_delta = (25, 25, 25)   (= grid_res / grid_size = 50/2)\n- num_cells  = 125000          (= 50^3)\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport os\nfrom typing import Optional, Tuple\n\nimport cupy\nimport numpy as np\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Grid constants\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nGRID_MIN = np.array([-1.0, -1.0, -1.0], dtype=np.float32)\nGRID_MAX = np.array([1.0, 1.0, 1.0], dtype=np.float32)\nCELL_SIZE = np.float32(0.04)\nGRID_RES = np.array([50, 50, 50], dtype=np.int32)\nGRID_DELTA = np.array([25.0, 25.0, 25.0], dtype=np.float32)  # grid_res / grid_size\nNUM_CELLS = 125_000  # 50 * 50 * 50\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Numpy dtype matching ``struct GridParams`` in common.cuh\n#\n# struct GridParams {\n#     float3 grid_min;    // 12 bytes\n#     float3 grid_max;    // 12 bytes\n#     int3   grid_res;    // 12 bytes\n#     float3 grid_delta;  // 12 bytes\n#     int    num_cells;   //  4 bytes\n# };                      // Total: 52 bytes\n#\n# CUDA float3/int3 are 12 bytes with no trailing pad. align=False required.\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nGRID_PARAMS_DTYPE = np.dtype(\n    [\n        (\"grid_min\", np.float32, (3,)),\n        (\"grid_max\", np.float32, (3,)),\n        (\"grid_res\", np.int32, (3,)),\n        (\"grid_delta\", np.float32, (3,)),\n        (\"num_cells\", np.int32),\n    ],\n    align=False,\n)\n\nassert GRID_PARAMS_DTYPE.itemsize == 52, (","numLines":60,"startLine":1,"totalLines":238}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DqeBa2u66y8NWXakyGFw9K","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→\"\"\"BuildDataStruct kernel for building cell start/end index tables.\n     2→\n     3→Compiles physics/kernels/build_grid.cu via CuPy RawModule and provides\n     4→a function to launch K_BuildDataStruct which detects cell boundaries in\n     5→the sorted hash array and populates cell_indexes_start / cell_indexes_end.\n     6→\n     7→Grid sizing (matches hash_sort.py)\n     8→-----------------------------------\n     9→- num_cells = 125000 (50^3)\n    10→- cell_indexes_start: uint32[num_cells], memset to 0xFFFFFFFF before each frame\n    11→- cell_indexes_end:   uint32[num_cells]\n    12→\"\"\"\n    13→\n    14→from __future__ import annotations\n    15→\n    16→import os\n    17→from typing import Optional, Tuple\n    18→\n    19→import cupy\n    20→import numpy as np\n    21→\n    22→from hash_sort import NUM_CELLS, build_grid_params\n    23→\n    24→# Sentinel value for empty cells (matches 0xFFFFFFFF memset).\n    25→EMPTY_CELL = np.uint32(0xFFFFFFFF)\n    26→\n    27→BLOCK_SIZE = 256\n    28→\n    29→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    30→# CuPy RawModule compilation\n    31→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    32→\n    33→_module: Optional[object] = None\n    34→\n    35→\n    36→def _ensure_ptx_if_needed() -> None:\n    37→    \"\"\"Force PTX compilation when GPU arch exceeds NVRTC's max sm target.\"\"\"\n    38→    from cupy.cuda import compiler as _compiler\n    39→    from cupy.cuda import device as _device\n    40→\n    41→    gpu_cc = _device.Device().compute_capability\n    42→    nvrtc_max = _compiler._get_max_compute_capability()\n    43→    if int(gpu_cc) > int(nvrtc_max):\n    44→        _compiler._use_ptx = True\n    45→        if hasattr(_compiler._get_arch_for_options_for_nvrtc, \"_cache\"):\n    46→            _compiler._get_arch_for_options_for_nvrtc._cache = {}\n    47→        if hasattr(_compiler._get_arch, \"_cache\"):\n    48→            _compiler._get_arch._cache = {}\n    49→\n    50→\n    51→def _get_module() -> \"object\":\n    52→    \"\"\"Compile (or return cached) CuPy RawModule from build_grid.cu.\"\"\"\n    53→    global _module\n    54→    if _module is not None:\n    55→        return _module\n    56→\n    57→    _ensure_ptx_if_needed()\n    58→\n    59→    kernel_dir = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \"physics\", \"kernels\")\n    60→    cu_path = os.path.join(kernel_dir, \"build_grid.cu\")\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e01bb850-3d98-461b-825e-005d7a10b01f","uuid":"21dc5bc0-42af-413c-9f9e-b5db9134f072","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/build_grid.py","content":"\"\"\"BuildDataStruct kernel for building cell start/end index tables.\n\nCompiles physics/kernels/build_grid.cu via CuPy RawModule and provides\na function to launch K_BuildDataStruct which detects cell boundaries in\nthe sorted hash array and populates cell_indexes_start / cell_indexes_end.\n\nGrid sizing (matches hash_sort.py)\n-----------------------------------\n- num_cells = 125000 (50^3)\n- cell_indexes_start: uint32[num_cells], memset to 0xFFFFFFFF before each frame\n- cell_indexes_end:   uint32[num_cells]\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport os\nfrom typing import Optional, Tuple\n\nimport cupy\nimport numpy as np\n\nfrom hash_sort import NUM_CELLS, build_grid_params\n\n# Sentinel value for empty cells (matches 0xFFFFFFFF memset).\nEMPTY_CELL = np.uint32(0xFFFFFFFF)\n\nBLOCK_SIZE = 256\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# CuPy RawModule compilation\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n_module: Optional[object] = None\n\n\ndef _ensure_ptx_if_needed() -> None:\n    \"\"\"Force PTX compilation when GPU arch exceeds NVRTC's max sm target.\"\"\"\n    from cupy.cuda import compiler as _compiler\n    from cupy.cuda import device as _device\n\n    gpu_cc = _device.Device().compute_capability\n    nvrtc_max = _compiler._get_max_compute_capability()\n    if int(gpu_cc) > int(nvrtc_max):\n        _compiler._use_ptx = True\n        if hasattr(_compiler._get_arch_for_options_for_nvrtc, \"_cache\"):\n            _compiler._get_arch_for_options_for_nvrtc._cache = {}\n        if hasattr(_compiler._get_arch, \"_cache\"):\n            _compiler._get_arch._cache = {}\n\n\ndef _get_module() -> \"object\":\n    \"\"\"Compile (or return cached) CuPy RawModule from build_grid.cu.\"\"\"\n    global _module\n    if _module is not None:\n        return _module\n\n    _ensure_ptx_if_needed()\n\n    kernel_dir = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \"physics\", \"kernels\")\n    cu_path = os.path.join(kernel_dir, \"build_grid.cu\")","numLines":60,"startLine":1,"totalLines":171}}}
