{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LjKfV5YqHBsWVBaXZX5xT1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→\"\"\"Integration test for integrate.py -- K_Integrate kernel.\n     2→\n     3→Acceptance criteria:\n     4→  - Symplectic Euler: vel_new = vel + dt * accel; pos_new uses XSPH for FLUID\n     5→  - Impulse SDF boundary: 6 planes of box (-1,-1,-1) to (1,1,1), restitution=0.3,\n     6→    Coulomb friction mu_wall=0.5\n     7→  - STATIC particles skipped (position unchanged)\n     8→  - GAS buoyancy: beta=0.01 * (T-293) * (0, 9.81, 0)\n     9→  - GAS drag: vel *= (1 - 2.0 * dt)\n    10→  - Velocity clamp at 50.0\n    11→  - Color from c_materials, tinted red for T>293K, faded by health\n    12→  - Writeback to UNSORTED arrays via sort_indexes\n    13→  - Bounce test: particle dropped from height bounces and loses energy\n    14→  - 10K water pool test: no NaN after 1000 steps\n    15→  - Block size = 256, 500K stress test\n    16→\n    17→Requirements: cupy, numpy, an NVIDIA GPU with CUDA 12.x.\n    18→\"\"\"\n    19→\n    20→from __future__ import annotations\n    21→\n    22→import math\n    23→import os\n    24→import sys\n    25→\n    26→sys.path.insert(0, os.path.dirname(__file__))\n    27→\n    28→import cupy\n    29→import numpy as np\n    30→\n    31→from step1 import (\n    32→    SIM_PARAMS_DTYPE,\n    33→    build_sim_params,\n    34→)\n    35→from materials import (\n    36→    FLUID,\n    37→    GRANULAR,\n    38→    GAS,\n    39→    STATIC,\n    40→    WATER,\n    41→    SAND,\n    42→    STEAM,\n    43→    STONE,\n    44→    build_material_array,\n    45→)\n    46→from integrate import (\n    47→    BLOCK_SIZE,\n    48→    get_module,\n    49→    integrate,\n    50→    upload_materials,\n    51→    upload_sim_params,\n    52→)\n    53→\n    54→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    55→# Constants\n    56→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------