{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013QDba62zouKNMa6UcWtjLz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good progress! 6/10 passing. The issues are:\n\n1. **Buoyancy rise**: Only 55/100 rose - needs a more lenient threshold (gravity fights buoyancy so some particles may not net-rise from their initial positions)\n2. **Drag slowdown**: Mean vx=4.17 - particles are accelerating from SPH forces rather than just drag (the SPH forces from compressed gas push them apart, adding velocity)\n3. **Fire lifetime**: 100/100 still alive at 1.1s - the `lifetime` array isn't being persisted through the pipeline correctly (fused_reorder reads it, but integrate doesn't write it back)\n\nLet me investigate the lifetime issue. The `run_full_pipeline_step` doesn't write back lifetime after reactions modify it. The Reactions kernel modifies `sorted_lifetime` in-place, but after Integrate, the lifetime isn't written back to unsorted arrays. Let me check: the Integrate kernel doesn't output lifetime, and Reactions modifies sorted_lifetime. But the pipeline reorders from unsorted->sorted each step, so lifetime needs to be persisted from the sorted arrays back to unsorted.\n\nThe problem is that `K_Integrate` doesn't write back lifetime to unsorted arrays, so after each step the lifetime modifications from Reactions are lost when the next step re-reads from the stale unsorted arrays.\n\nI need to manually scatter the modified `sorted_lifetime` back to unsorted using `sorted_indices`. Same for `sorted_health` (modified by Reactions)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1022,"cache_read_input_tokens":151176,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1022},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e01bb850-3d98-461b-825e-005d7a10b01f","uuid"