vel, exp_heat, exp_corrode, frame=frame,\n    )\n\n    # Step2\n    sph_force, veleval_out = compute_step2(\n        sorted_pos, sorted_vel, density, sorted_mass, sorted_pi,\n        cell_start, cell_end,\n    )\n\n    # Integrate\n    pos_out, vel_out, color_out, pi_out, sc_out, temp_out = integrate(\n        sorted_pos, sorted_vel, veleval_out, sph_force,\n        sorted_mass, sorted_pi, sorted_temp, sorted_health,","numLines":70,"startLine":186,"totalLines":913}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Q6FpRq6o1FfGQrd7Kburvy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see the issue! Look at line 252: the `integrate` call passes `sorted_pi` (which was modified by Reactions to set DEAD for expired particles). But the Integrate kernel writes `packed_info_out[orig_idx] = pi` where `pi = sorted_packed_info[i]`. So particles that were killed by Reactions (packed_info set to DEAD) should be written back correctly.\n\nWait, but for the lifetime case, the Reactions kernel does:\n1. `lt -= dt` (subtract dt)\n2. If `lt <= 0`: set packed_info to DEAD, set lifetime=0, health=0\n\nSo after 1000 steps, `lt = 1.0 - 1000*0.001 = 0.0`. At step 1000, `lt -= 0.001` gives `lt = -0.001`, so `lt <= 0.0f` triggers and the particle dies.\n\nBut wait - the Reactions kernel is called with `sorted_lifetime` which was populated by `fused_reorder` from `w[\"lifetime\"]`. And `w[\"lifetime\"]` is updated each step from the sorted_lifetime writeback. So after each step, `w[\"lifetime\"]` should reflect the decremented values.\n\nLet me add a quick debug test:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1739,"cache_read_input_tokens":157020,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1739},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e01bb850-3d98-461b-825e-005d7a10b01f","uuid":"97a6db48-d6bb-439c-8ec9-ea8822d5fa67"}
